Project 36) Project 36: Swarm Microbot System for Environmental Manipulation (2025)

Core mechanism: A swarm of 300-micrometer magnetic robots that float on fluid surfaces. Controlled by external oscillating magnetic fields. The swarm creates hydrodynamic flows that can move passive objects, rotate gears, and manipulate the surrounding fluid without physical contact .

Variants:

Hydro Swarm: Water-surface bots that generate currents to move floating objects

Thermo Swarm: Gas-liquid phase change bots that expand/contract to apply force 

Photo Swarm: Light-powered bots that degrade chemicals in water 

Limitations:

Cannot "control" elements in the bending sense

Requires liquid medium (water) for most functions

Magnetic control limits range and precision

Not suitable for "blood bending" – human blood is not water, and internal use requires medical approval
